&lt;p&gt;Sometimes physicality is in order by putting your fingertips to pages. Flipping through printed materials can be very therapeutic and inspiring. From magazines like &lt;a href=&quot;http://layersmagazine.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; title=&quot;Layers&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Layers&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.printmag.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; title=&quot;Print&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Print&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.cmykmag.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; title=&quot;CMYK&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;CMYK&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.commarts.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; title=&quot;Communication Arts&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Communication Arts&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.creativebloq.com/computer-arts-magazine&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; title=&quot;Computer Arts&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Computer Arts&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to books such as, &amp;ldquo;&lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.amazon.com/Typography-Friedrich-Friedl/dp/1579120237&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; title=&quot;Typography by Friedrich Friedl&quot;&gt;Typography: An Encyclopedic Survey of Type Design and Techniques Throughout History&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&amp;rdquo; by Friedrich Friedl, Nicolaus Ott, and Bernard Stein.&lt;/p&gt;

