&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.digitalmusicnews.com/2016/04/26/tidal-subscriptions-surge-after-beyonce-lemonade-exclusive/&quot;&gt;http://www.digitalmusicnews.com/2016/04/26/tidal-subscriptions-surge-after-beyonce-lemonade-exclusive/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.bbc.com/news/business-34324772&quot;&gt;http://www.bbc.com/news/business-34324772&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.usatoday.com/story/opinion/2016/04/25/prince-purple-rain-darling-nikki-censorship-lyrics-tipper-gore-column/83466774/&quot;&gt;http://www.usatoday.com/story/opinion/2016/04/25/prince-purple-rain-darling-nikki-censorship-lyrics-tipper-gore-column/83466774/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The undeniable presence of social media in today&amp;rsquo;s digital landscape continues to change the way we use the Internet, interact with each other, and experience advertising messages. Social Media has transcended the confines of the millennial audience pushing out to a wider variety of ages and cultures with each passing year. Here I will summarize the current state of one of the most popular and influential social networks currently making waves in cyber space.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Facebook&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;In the blue corner weighing in at 1.32 billion active users is the titan of social networks, Facebook. These days you would be hard-pressed to find someone who is not an active Facebook user; in the beginning Facebook was for college students primarily but has now grown to have adults age 35-54 as the largest age group of users. Enter 2016, the beginning of true digital dominance in the Advertising Industry, Facebook&amp;rsquo;s Mark Zuckerberg has laid out a bold new plan for the already dominating social network. The Messenger Platform that works through Facebook is getting an upgrade in the form of automated bots. These chatbots are able to walk you through making online purchases as well as getting the weather forecast, keeping up with current events and more, all without having to leave Facebook Messenger. Some are complaining that the bots are creating spam in Messenger and there seem to be bugs that need addressing.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;As technology continues to advance and shape the world no frontier is left untouched, this rings true for Facebook also as it has also been revealed that they hope to make group hangouts through virtual reality a common occurrence. Imagine being able to interact with friends from other states and even countries face-to-face in a virtual realm, where Zuckerberg also intends to implement touch controls that would theoretically allow you to reach out and &amp;ldquo;touch&amp;rdquo; others in said virtual space. Facebook is developing more sophisticated 360 degree cameras to further facilitate Facebook&amp;rsquo;s virtual reality involvement.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2016 will yield many more changes to the ever evolving social media landscape and Facebook will no doubt be at the center of it all. Advertising opportunities will increase, new content will arise, and the total number of users will likely to grow to largest size so far.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;As generations keep changing, the nature of advertisement and media is also changing. In previous generations, the logic of marketing was that more the number of advertisements you throw at youngsters, the sooner you could hook them to your brand. During those times, this approach actually made some sense, but now, reaching out to the younger generation takes a lot more than traditional ads.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;In particular, the millennials (born from early 80&amp;rsquo;s to around 2000) prove to be a challenge for the market and you can see numerous companies attempting to connect with them to seek personal, deep, and long-lasting relationships. Today, they are more like digital natives who are hooked on to their tablets, smartphones, and laptops. The goal for most marketers today is to reach out to millennials in the best ways so they can get loyalty, attention and ultimately make profits.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1 dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Best Advertising Strategies to Target Millennials&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Timing and location is crucial when getting the message across to millennials about your brand. If your business is the sort that wishes to target this heavy group, you must be aware of the fact that millennials spend most of their time on the internet. That&amp;rsquo;s where you can target them.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1 dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Social Media&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;With the internet common in the present century, it isn&amp;rsquo;t anything new to see that millennials depend on social media sites. The more information they find on social platforms like Twitter, Facebook, Snapchat and many others, the more they tend to trust and act on that information. In other words, social media for advertisers can serve as one of the best places to target millennials.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1 dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Internet Content Matters&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Another good strategy to reach millennials is through content. Marketers these days invest a lot of their time putting their message across to youngsters via content. In a recent survey, as much as 62 percent of millennials agreed that they read or watch a majority of their content online via social media and different websites. &amp;nbsp;By content, this could include articles, blogs, and other various web-based postings. When millennials read content online, they tend to relate more and somehow trust it more than watching or listening to ads.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1 dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Millennials Depend On Reviews Not Ads&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;In previous generations, people would simply watch ads on the television and their loyalty to the brand was a guarantee. Today, things have changed drastically and millennials tend to depend more on the reviews of products they see on the internet. &amp;nbsp;Meaning, investments in social media and reputation management are more important now than ever to the young buyers of today. &amp;nbsp;It&amp;rsquo;s also not about how the product appears on television, but how it can affect their life. They need to see proof that what you offer them can actually have an impact on their life.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h1 dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Millennials Focus on Specific Categories&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Many researches also reveal that although millennials are tech advanced, there are some things that just don&amp;rsquo;t change. In terms of categories, male millennials still search for tech based gadgets and sports content while female millennials still focus on beauty and health aids. Keeping these traditions in mind, businesses should continue to work on displaying their services or products in this space.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Authenticity and guarantee of advertising comes when you speak to and perceive millennials in the way they wish to be seen or viewed. You have to cultivate an authentic relationship and soon you can reap the rewards.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to Google, there are 5 &amp;quot;moments&amp;quot; in auto shopping. These moments are when shoppers make a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;decision&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;about these critical requirements before they purchase. These moments determine what they will consider and where they want to buy.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHICH CAR IS BEST?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Research reveals shoppers are most influenced by customer reviews and&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;prefer watching videos&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;to inform their buying process. Customers know exactly why they believe their vehicle is the best and can share their shopping experiences with current shoppers.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IS IT RIGHT FOR ME?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Video usage ranks highly at this stage. The top types of videos auto shoppers search for include vehicle&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;test drives&lt;/strong&gt;, highlights of&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;features and options&lt;/strong&gt;, and&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;walkthroughs&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the interior or exterior of the vehicle.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CAN I AFFORD IT?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Google says, &amp;quot;Once consumers can imagine owning a particular vehicle, they need to know if they can afford it. Also, for many shoppers, the value of their current car is just as important as the price of the new one.&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHO SHOULD I BUY FROM?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Happy customers not only know and trust their dealership,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;they&amp;#39;re willing to tell others&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;because they often feel a debt of gratitude towards the dealership and their salesperson.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;5)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IS IT A FAIR DEAL?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;When a store operates with transparency and salespeople create relationships based on trust,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;buyers relax and focus&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;on getting what they want. Nothing says, &amp;quot;I got a fair deal&amp;quot; like being happy with your purchase.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So why is it critical that dealers strive to own these 5 moments? Because the average car shopper today makes less than two dealership visits before they buy. That&amp;#39;s why you need customer videos to help them decide to visit your store&amp;nbsp;first. It&amp;#39;s one thing to promise a great customer experience, now you can prove it with customer videos.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As a Mom/Cheer Coach/Office Manager, I cannot count the times I have said &amp;ldquo;fake it &amp;lsquo;til you make it&amp;rdquo; to my &amp;ldquo;people&amp;rdquo;. &amp;nbsp;Sometimes they just &amp;ldquo;aren&amp;rsquo;t feeling it&amp;rdquo; and need a quick attitude adjustment.&amp;nbsp; That is when I step in say the magical phrase that reminds them to make a conscious choice to &amp;ldquo;pretend&amp;rdquo; until it becomes &amp;ldquo;real&amp;rdquo;.&amp;nbsp; It all starts with a smile.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I believe smiling is crucial when answering the phone. &amp;nbsp;People can hear a smile or frump through the phone.&amp;nbsp; &lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;The reason is not psychological but rather physiological.&amp;nbsp; When you smile, the soft palate at the back of your mouth raises and makes the sound waves more fluid and helps your voice to sound friendly, warm, and receptive.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/em&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Too many times we are distracted and answer the phone without consciously thinking and putting a smile on our face.&amp;nbsp; This can be a costly mistake.&amp;nbsp; For example, if a potential client calls and is greeted by a frumpy monotone voice, it will translate negatively and does not instill immediate confidence in you or your company. If a coworker calls your extension and you answer without smiling, it can give the impression that they are irritating you or annoying you with their call - which may or may not be true - but it is definitely not acceptable behavior in a professional work environment and can affect the all-around culture of a company.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On the flip side, when you greet a potential client on the phone with a literal smile on your face, you exude confidence; you make them feel like they are important to you and that they can trust you.&amp;nbsp; A call answered with a smile by a coworker can change the attitude of the caller in an instant and can make a much more positive work environment.&amp;nbsp; Zappos.com gets it.&amp;nbsp; If you call and hear &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uo3sMaH-h9Mv&quot;&gt;this &lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;- how can you keep from smiling back?&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;ldquo;Some telemarketing companies are so convinced of the value of smiling when talking on the phone that they install mirrors above telemarketers&amp;#39; desks to remind them to smile.&amp;rdquo;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/em&gt;I would add that a strategically placed mirror would also relieve the stress of your coworkers having to tell you when you have erroneous food items stuck in your teeth, but I digress&amp;hellip;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, fake it &amp;lsquo;til you make it, put a smile on your face/ in your voice and make the world a better place, one smile at a time!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(Quotes in italics found in &amp;ldquo;topics: other business skills&amp;rdquo; on www.dummies.com)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I get this question quite a bit and it&amp;rsquo;s definitely changed over the years.&amp;nbsp; In fact, it&amp;rsquo;s different every time I get it asked to me.&amp;nbsp; My refrain is this, &amp;lsquo;If it was my marketing budget, what would I do?&amp;rsquo;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Of course this comes with the assumption that I know YOUR marketplace.&amp;nbsp; And that&amp;rsquo;s a big if.&amp;nbsp; I see a lot of vendors that sell one or two of the following; SEM, SEO, video, creative, email&amp;rsquo;s or traditional media.&amp;nbsp; But how much do they know a client&amp;rsquo;s market?&amp;nbsp; If they sell online attributes, how much do they know about your creative execution?&amp;nbsp; If they know traditional, what do they know about your online audience?&amp;nbsp; If you want reassess your marketing to determine a budget, below are five categories to consider.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;What&amp;rsquo;s your trade area?
	&lt;ol style=&quot;list-style-type:lower-alpha;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Don&amp;rsquo;t know?&amp;nbsp; Start by looking at a map of you vs. your competitors.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Check your Google Analytics for your online footprint.&amp;nbsp; How much traffic is coming each month?&amp;nbsp; How does compare to my competitors.&amp;nbsp; Where are your sessions coming from geographically and referrals?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Sales by zip codes will help you discover opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ol&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Who&amp;rsquo;s your competition?&amp;nbsp; There are 2 areas to consider;
	&lt;ol style=&quot;list-style-type:lower-alpha;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Online and off line.
		&lt;ol style=&quot;list-style-type:lower-roman;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;If you determined your trade area, you should be able to tackle this easily. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Now check the competitions selling props and where they are spending their ad budgets.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ol&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ol&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;What are your goals?
	&lt;ol style=&quot;list-style-type:lower-alpha;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Do you have a sales objective? What&amp;rsquo;s your closing percentage?&amp;nbsp; You can usually back into your budget based on rudimentary math.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Maintain or grow market share?&amp;nbsp; Be truthful.&amp;nbsp; Volume leader or profitability?&amp;nbsp; Be true to yourself when answering this.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ol&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;What DMA are you in?
	&lt;ol style=&quot;list-style-type:lower-alpha;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Depending on the size of your media market will determine whether you can afford traditional media or strictly online media.&amp;nbsp; The rule of thumb is the larger the area, the lower the CPM.&amp;nbsp; But if you live in a major metro, you will waste money if your trade area doesn&amp;rsquo;t cover at least 50% of the DMA.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Unless your Unique Selling Proposition is a game changer, not very many customers will drive past 2-3 other competitors to get to your store.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ol&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;What&amp;rsquo;s your USP?&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ol style=&quot;list-style-type:lower-alpha;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;And don&amp;rsquo;t tell me we treat our customers better.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; That&amp;rsquo;s great for getting them to come back.&amp;nbsp; I want to know if you have a unique selling proposition and if not, you need one.&amp;nbsp; Check other markets if you don&amp;rsquo;t have one?&amp;nbsp; It may not be unique to your vertical but may be to your market.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ol&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:1.0in;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After you&amp;rsquo;ve gathered the above five items, you will be able to begin formulating a marketing plan with a fiscally responsible budget to follow month in and out.&amp;nbsp; If your vendor isn&amp;rsquo;t asking you these questions or giving you this information, then they aren&amp;rsquo;t really interested in growing your market.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you truly ready to answer them, give us a call and we&amp;rsquo;ll help you along the way.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

